[1]Design and developmentThe Societa Idrovolanti Alta Italia (SIAI) was formed in 1915 initially to build French flying-boats under license.
[2]The company employed Rafaele Conflenti as Chief Designer and his first design was the SIAI S.8 a two-seat equal-span biplane flying boat first flown in 1917.
[3]The Royal Italian Navy ordered 800 S.8s to be built by SIAI and sub-contractors.
[4]With the end of the war production was stopped when 172 aircraft had been delivered.
[5]Early aircraft were powered by an Isotta Fraschini V4B engine, later aircraft had the more powerful 220 hp (164 kW) Hispano-Suiza 44.
